text:
Good morning marketers! I was introduced to the group by the fabulous <@U01DEA6F7CH>. I'm already impressed by how considerate and friendly everyone is in the channels.

I established my B2B writing studio in 2013, specializing in the tech, HR, retail/ecom, and higher ed industries. But I fell in love with the content development process and teaching other writers how to tap into this successful and stable career path.

Last year I focused my efforts on growing the B2B Writing Institute to bring more standards and resources to writers navigating this amazing field. Which I hope will end up serving you all by making it easier to find qualified, talented B2B writers! :black_nib:

(The pen is relevant because I have my very first fountain pen arriving today! Any other hand lettering nerds out there with tips for how to use it?)

Hi folks! Looong over due, but better late than never amirite? I’m Bud. I’m currently the Content Manager at CXL (<http://CXL.com|CXL.com>) — an education platform that helps train some of the world’s best marketers. :slightly_smiling_face: Prior to CXL, I was doing freelance content marketing and strategy for a variety of small businesses and brands. Excited to connect with everyone here, and really take my content marketing skills to the next level. Always open to DM here or chat elsewhere. I’m @aboundlessworld on Twitter.

Fun fact — I traded Gary Vaynerchuk 5 SNES games for my first job interview at Vayermedia (and got the job)
